<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN ONOFRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man was struck by a car and killed as he ran across Interstate 
5 on Saturday night, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The man was hit by a northbound car about 11:45 p.m., Deputy Coroner Max Murphy 
said, about three miles south of the Basilone Road exit. The victim was dead at 
the scene, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the car was not cited, according to the California Highway 
Patrol, which is investigating the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
