<P>
TURNER TAKES ONE-STROKE LEAD IN L.A. CITY GOLF CHAMPIONSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southpaw Mike Turner of Woodland Hills shot a one-under-par 71 on the Griffith 
Park Wilson course Sunday to take a one-stroke lead after 36 holes of the Los 
Angeles City Golf Championships. 
</P>
<P>
Turner, the 1987 champion, was at 139. Ken Cruz of Yorba Linda, who was tied 
for the lead with Turner after Saturday's first round, was at 140. 
</P>
<P>
The final 36 holes are scheduled next Saturday and Sunday at Rancho Park. 
</P>
