NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A surprised Chip Hanauer took advantage of favored Miss Budweiser's first-lap 
mishap and drove the Miss Circus Circus to victory in the Madison Regatta for 
unlimited hydroplanes at Madison, Ind. 
</P>
<P>
Tom D'Eath's Miss Budweiser, winner of 13 of the previous 15 heats of 
competition this season, grabbed the lead at the start but hit a wave in the 
rough Ohio River going through the second turn and lifted off the water. 
</P>
<P>
By the time he came down, Hanauer had ducked inside for the lead and stayed in 
front for the rest of the five-lap race. 
</P>
<P>
Hanauer averaged 126.516 m.p.h. for the five laps. Despite some damage to his 
boat, D'Eath finished second at 121.028 m.p.h. 
</P>
