<HEADLINE>
<P>
FETTERS, FRASER ANGELS OF WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pitchers Mike Fetters and Willie Fraser, who gave strong performances in middle 
relief, have been named Angels of the Week by The Times' Orange County Edition. 
</P>
<P>
Fetters earned his first major league victory Saturday by pitching the last two 
innings of the Angels' 11-inning, 4-3 victory at Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
He also pitched two innings at Cleveland and 1 1/3 innings at Toronto and did 
not allow an earned run in his three appearances. His ERA has fallen to 3.90. 
</P>
<P>
Fraser pitched five innings Friday, his longest outing in two years, to help 
the Angels defeat Milwaukee, 9-8, in 16 innings. He also pitched 2 1/3 
scoreless innings at Toronto and lowered his ERA to 4.60. 
</P>
<P>
A check for $250 in Fetters' and Fraser's names will be given to the Boys and 
Girls Clubs of Orange County. 
</P>
