<P>
French Businessman Buys Adidas: Flamboyant French businessman and soccer club 
owner Bernard Tapie bought control of Adidas, the West German sportswear 
manufacturing giant. Gerhard Ziener, president of Adidas' supervisory board, 
said 80% of the share capital, owned by the heirs of company founder Adi 
Dassler, will be transferred to Bernard Tapie Finance S.A. of Paris. The 
company, with $2.8 billion in sales last year, is the largest sporting goods 
manufacturer in the world. 
