LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
BOY, 15, ARRESTED IN STANTON IN CONNECTION WITH GANG KILLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a dawn raid on a Stanton gang stronghold, police arrested a 15-year-old boy 
on suspicion of murdering Rosendo Ibarra, a 17-year-old shot in the head while 
talking to his girlfriend on the telephone. 
</P>
<P>
Two other suspects in the April murder, including the man police believe pulled 
the trigger, were not at home. 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove police were still searching for them early this afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Police believe the 15-year-old, whose name was not released because of his age, 
helped plan Ibarra's murder. 
</P>
<P>
"He took part in the conspiracy, and we believe he went with the fellows that 
did it and walked right up with the shooter," said Detective Mike Handfield of 
the Garden Grove Police. 
</P>
<P>
The killing was believed to be the latest spasm in a decades-old dispute 
between residents of the Rose Street neighborhood in Stanton and the La Colonia 
neighborhood in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Ibarra, a construction worker who lived in La Colonia, was gunned down at a pay 
phone in a Garden Grove shopping center across the street from his home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
